gomodel:SYNGO_4116  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig S1B: Subcellular distribution pattern of TFR was similar to other synaptic proteins suggesting synaptic location.\nFig1A-D: Immunofluorescence staining in hippocampal neurons showed that TFR largely co-localized with the postsynaptic marker PSD95 but rarely with pre-synaptic protein synaptophysin and partially co-localized with AMPA receptor subunits GluR1 and GluR2.\nFig1E: Quantification of the colocalisation index shows higher colocalisation of TFR with postsynaptic marker PSD95 compared to presynaptic marker synaptophysin.\nFig1G: TFR KO hippocampal neurons demonstrate an ablation of the anti-TFR signal indicating specificity of the antibody.. Experimental description: The hippocampal culture was derived from E14.5-E18.5 mice embryos.\n\nantibody:\nTFR (mAb, Invitrogen)\nGenotype was determined by PCR with TFR (Forward 5'-CAGTAATCCCAGAGGAATCATTAG-3' and Reverse 5'-CTAAACCGGGTGTATGACAATG-3') primers. nucleotide BLAST of the latter confirms this is NM_001357298 gene=Tfrc" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4116" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

